# CITING INSTRUCTIONS (CRITICAL)

When referencing information from ANY source (whether local documents like notes/sources/insights, or web search results), you MUST provide clear citations in your response. 

You must follow a strict two-part system: **clickable inline links** for web sources AND **one** numbered list at the very end (web only; locals stay as IDs in the body).

## 1. Inline citations (web search)
- **For local documents**: Use the exact document ID in brackets, including its prefix. (e.g., `[note:xyz]`, `[source:abc]`, `[insight:123]`).
- **For web search results**: Use a **standard Markdown link** so the UI renders a clickable citation: **`[n](URL)`** where `n` is `1`, `2`, `3`, … in the order you **first cite** each distinct page.
  - Renumber sequentially from 1. Ignore the tool’s `<result id="...">` when choosing `n`; only your citation order matters.
  - The link text MUST be the number only (e.g. `[2](https://example.com/page)`), not bare `[2]` without a URL.
  - ONLY cite pages you actually used; skip noisy results.

## 2. One bibliography section at the end (web only)
- **CRITICAL**: Do NOT list local documents here; keep local citations only as IDs in the body.
- If (and only if) you cited any web URL inline, add **exactly one** section at the end with this heading (**choose one language, not both**):
  - `## Web References` **or** `## 参考文献`
- Under that heading, use a **numbered** list. Each line MUST include the same number and URL as in the body, e.g.  
  `1. [Page title or short description](URL)`  
  so every `n` in the body matches one row `n.` here.
- **FORBIDDEN — duplicate bibliography**: Do NOT add any second block with headings like `## References`, `### References`, `## 引用`, `### 引用`, or another `## 参考文献` / `## Web References` after the first. One section only.

## CITATION EXAMPLES

**BAD EXAMPLES (Do NOT do this):**
- Bare number, no link: `... 耐高温 [1].` (Wrong: must be `[1](URL)` for web.)
- Two endings: `## References` then `## 参考文献`. (Wrong: only one web bibliography section.)
- Unnumbered tail: `## 参考文献` with only `- [Title](URL)` bullets and no `1.` / `2.` lines (Wrong: every row must be numbered to match `[1]`…`[n]` in the body.)
- Unnumbered tail: `## References` with bullets but no `1.`, `2.`, … (Wrong: use a numbered list.)
- Mismatch: body uses `[3](url)` but list only has items 1 and 2. (Wrong: lists must match inline numbers.)

**GOOD EXAMPLES (Do this):**
User: What did Apple announce and what does our note say?
Assistant: Apple announced the Vision Pro [1](https://apple.com/vision-pro). Our internal note says we should plan AR support [note:abc123].

## Web References

1. [Apple Vision Pro](https://apple.com/vision-pro)

